<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Unexpected-Eof on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/unexpected-eof/</link><description>Recent content in Unexpected-Eof on ErrorCode — Error Code Reference &amp; Solutions</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/tags/unexpected-eof/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>[Solution] Bash Unexpected End of File (Unmatched Quote)</title><link>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/bash/unmatched-quote/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://errorcode.excellentwiki.com/languages/bash/unmatched-quote/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="bash-unexpected-end-of-file-unmatched-quote-fix"&gt;Bash Unexpected End of File (Unmatched Quote) Fix&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This error occurs when Bash reaches the end of input while still inside an unclosed quote, command substitution, or other delimited construct.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="description"&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Bash tracks open quotes, parentheses, braces, and command substitutions. If input ends before these are closed, Bash reports an unexpected end of file. The most common cause is a missing closing quote.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="common-causes"&gt;Common Causes&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Unclosed double or single quote&lt;/strong&gt; — the opening &lt;code&gt;&amp;quot;&lt;/code&gt; or &lt;code&gt;'&lt;/code&gt; has no matching closer.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Missing closing bracket&lt;/strong&gt; — &lt;code&gt;$(command&lt;/code&gt; without &lt;code&gt;)&lt;/code&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Incomplete here-document&lt;/strong&gt; — missing &lt;code&gt;EOF&lt;/code&gt; delimiter.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Multi-line string without proper continuation&lt;/strong&gt; — forgetting the closing delimiter.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="how-to-fix"&gt;How to Fix&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3 id="fix-1-find-and-close-unclosed-quotes"&gt;Fix 1: Find and close unclosed quotes&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Wrong&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;msg&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;Hello world
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;# Right
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;msg=&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;Hello world&lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-2-close-command-substitutions"&gt;Fix 2: Close command substitutions&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;div class="highlight"&gt;&lt;pre tabindex="0" style="color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;"&gt;&lt;code class="language-bash" data-lang="bash"&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Wrong&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;result&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;$(&lt;/span&gt;echo &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;test&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#75715e"&gt;# Right&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="display:flex;"&gt;&lt;span&gt;result&lt;span style="color:#f92672"&gt;=&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;$(&lt;/span&gt;echo &lt;span style="color:#e6db74"&gt;&amp;#34;test&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style="color:#66d9ef"&gt;)&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;h3 id="fix-3-use-syntax-highlighting-to-spot-mismatches"&gt;Fix 3: Use syntax highlighting to spot mismatches&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Most editors highlight matching quotes and brackets. Enable it to visually track unclosed delimiters.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item></channel></rss>